<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Projects | Bergen Linux User Group</title><link>https://www.blug.linux.no/project/</link><atom:link href="https://www.blug.linux.no/project/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><description>Projects</description><generator>Hugo Blox Builder (https://hugoblox.com)</generator><language>en-US</language><copyright>© 2017 BLUG</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sat, 28 Apr 2001 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><image><url>https://www.blug.linux.no/media/icon_hu_526dddd7da589f21.png</url><title>Projects</title><link>https://www.blug.linux.no/project/</link></image><item><title>RFC 1149</title><link>https://www.blug.linux.no/project/rfc1149/</link><pubDate>Sat, 28 Apr 2001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.blug.linux.no/project/rfc1149/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;11 years ago, April 1st 1990, rfc 1149 was written. This rfc specifies a protocol for IP over avian carriers, CPIP (carrier pigeon internet protocol). In 11 years, noone has bothered to implement this important protocol stack. But happily, we don&amp;rsquo;t need to wait any longer! BLUG in cooperation with &lt;a href="http://dueforening.tripod.com/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Vesta Brevdueforening&lt;/a&gt; has given you rfc 1149 support for Linux.&lt;/p&gt;
